</p></li></ul></context><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li id="LI_53184B16D403439F881DA2AB90C20E0F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Power off the system</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">On the operator panel, tap on the [System] icon on the right. Tap on [Power management]. Tap on [Power off]. The system shuts down. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Switch off the power supply</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the system has shut down, pull to open the cover under the roll winder. Switch the power switch to the 'off' position. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Unplug the mains cables. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the cover below the media drawer 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="24DISA050" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-87DBD356-A13A-44A7-B799-70CBF324AF9D.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>24 How to remove the cover below the media drawer</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_2A7CF94498F443518825F87BF30E279F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the media output lower cover. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="24DISA028" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F2EFC6F8-A9AE-449E-B6F0-0C3A8EC8B292.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>24 How to remove the media output lower cover</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_AF872F56095B4EBC963FCD3D016D0A0D" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_0F85C7CD6ECE40AAA6414F5D383EF9C1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
</p></li><li id="LI_90BAF8046B9E4C1986DF40F56573431C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Socket wrench 7 mm 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-7C62E86F-81E4-4340-9FC3-C81ADE2D02D8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6F0705C3-967F-408C-AD67-B11F81E61EAE-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6F0705C3-967F-408C-AD67-B11F81E61EAE-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_AB9EA5ED79304C20B72DFEA35068BA65" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_E50BF2C356D1449B807F19C082399D8A" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 2 screws (T20) of the power supply unit at the media drawer side. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_C3CA095615724D7C88854CE861AEA0FF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8E06318B-706A-4951-89A4-C93FE787ACF7-low.png" id="IMAGE_B83BF14092164FA8939907D828CE98C8" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8E06318B-706A-4951-89A4-C93FE787ACF7-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-51F53878-8462-4F9F-BCC5-1CF1946BF851" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-2E9BAFF0-AE3F-4197-9812-65EBC9AE75B5-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2E9BAFF0-AE3F-4197-9812-65EBC9AE75B5-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-C34741CC-836B-4BAF-9536-131A4109A51F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-525F7479-2B28-4BCD-8212-151D564358FE-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-525F7479-2B28-4BCD-8212-151D564358FE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the 3 plates (4 nuts and 4 screws) of the power box. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-9972626C-53E6-45B5-A495-4A55C30A4F97" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AA00357F-A855-4849-A254-C951E05F23E9-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AA00357F-A855-4849-A254-C951E05F23E9-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-B5B4D2CC-0B78-4CD2-922B-2DFFEEB67346" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F8786CA5-00EF-4D28-BBC7-E24524694F8F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F8786CA5-00EF-4D28-BBC7-E24524694F8F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the 2 connectors. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-EE72B00D-E10A-422D-BA23-A4F52076B3BE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C029244B-57C4-4679-94D0-99640BE732FD-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C029244B-57C4-4679-94D0-99640BE732FD-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the small plate (2 screws). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7AF6AFA9-5E58-4E74-9C53-EC40B4019E7E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-36D5D333-8618-4BBE-B74A-C5D94DC287BF-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-36D5D333-8618-4BBE-B74A-C5D94DC287BF-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide out the power box a little bit. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-42835212-587D-44A0-A8FE-8C0AA09433CD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5A07C04F-B1DF-44DC-9064-5CEE055DDFFF-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5A07C04F-B1DF-44DC-9064-5CEE055DDFFF-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Disconnect the 3 connectors at the left and right hand side. 
</p><note id="GUID-4C51DD81-4B5E-40F7-80F8-AE71EF7A07CF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The large connectors at the left hand side has a locking mechanism at the side. 
</p></note><note id="GUID-D7CEA12D-7917-4D19-ABB0-43E3E09930D1" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The power supply cables and connectors are marked. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-D24DAE0C-207D-420D-9F24-F4FC93286CDC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-190240A2-FB4E-48E4-83C3-79FA1BE189BE-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-190240A2-FB4E-48E4-83C3-79FA1BE189BE-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-DAAE86F0-08F6-4859-9ED3-170C8F66BA8B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0256A55E-E033-4940-81EC-064CE1804B0E-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0256A55E-E033-4940-81EC-064CE1804B0E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide out the power box completely. 
</p></li></ol><note type="caution" id="GUID-C7CE491E-908B-4859-AD5A-D552478C4C88" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Watch out and do not put it on your fingers. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-450C67B9-54AC-42C4-8048-978937FE761E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7B4A75AC-A1D8-4B62-9038-1D699FDE68A1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7B4A75AC-A1D8-4B62-9038-1D699FDE68A1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_E3FC7EE10DDC46BA880F87671551C890" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-28DD55D6-BAAF-44D6-8D16-AF98622103BF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The power supply cables and connectors are marked. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7CA589CA-02A1-4B23-97A7-E4A349FA6258" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1D54B8BB-AD22-48FC-B36B-42B950743351-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1D54B8BB-AD22-48FC-B36B-42B950743351-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5C4B92A8-575C-4245-83D5-3D2AA8FD31BA.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
